<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870513-0022 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Stone Container Corp.</HL><DD> 05/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> STO </IN><TEXT>   STONE CONTAINER CORP. shareholders at the annual meeting approved an increase in authorized common shares to 100 million from 60 million. The Chicago-based maker of paperboard and paper packaging products currently has about 19.9 million common shares outstanding. The additional shares will give Stone flexibility in connection with future stock splits, acquisitions and other corporate purposes, the company said. Holders also voted to change the state of incorporation to Delaware from Illinois. </TEXT></DOC>